quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,157,"Then produce your scripture, if you should be truthful."
  37,158,"And they have made [i.e., claimed] between Him and the jinn a lineage, but the jinn have already known that they [who made such claims] will be brought [to punishment]."
  37,159,"Exalted is Allāh above what they describe,"
  43,46,"And certainly did We send Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his establishment, and he said, "
  43,47,"But when he brought them Our signs, at once they laughed at them."
  43,48,"And We showed them not a sign except that it was greater than its sister, and We seized them with affliction that perhaps they might return [to faith]."
  44,31,"From Pharaoh. Indeed, he was a haughty one among the transgressors."
  44,32,"And We certainly chose them by knowledge over [all] the worlds."
  44,33,"And We gave them of signs that in which there was a clear trial."
  45,22,"And Allāh created the heavens and earth in truth and so that every soul may be recompensed for what it has earned, and they will not be wronged."
  45,23,"Have you seen he who has taken as his god his [own] desire, and Allāh has sent him astray due to knowledge{1} and has set a seal upon his hearing and his heart and put over his vision a veil? So who will guide him after Allāh? Then will you not be reminded?",1:[This can refer to Allāh's knowledge of that person and of his preference for his own inclinations or to that person's knowledge of the truth while he refuses it.]
  45,24,"And they say, ",1:[i.e., some people die and others live, replacing them.]
  46,10,"Say, ",1:[Based upon information from the Torah.],2:[The conclusion is estimated to be "...would you not then be the most unjust of people?" or "...in what condition would you then be?"]
  46,11,"And those who disbelieve say of those who believe, "
  46,12,"And before it was the scripture of Moses to lead and as a mercy. And this is a confirming Book in an Arabic tongue to warn those who have wronged and as good tidings to the doers of good."
  47,1,"Those who disbelieve and avert [people] from the way of Allāh - He will waste their deeds.{1}",1:[i.e., cause them to be lost or make them worthless, earning no reward.]
  47,2,"And those who believe and do righteous deeds and believe in what has been sent down upon Muḥammad - and it is the truth from their Lord - He will remove from them their misdeeds and amend their condition."
  47,3,"That is because those who disbelieve follow falsehood, and those who believe follow the truth from their Lord. Thus does Allāh present to the people their comparisons.{1}",1:[So that they may know the results of their choice.]
